reviews_data.review_text: Visiting from Atlanga, GA, and stopped here on the way to the city. Took 2 cappuccinos to go - very tasty coffee, rich in taste. The guy running running the shop was extremely nice!! Worth stopping by
Great coffee and great staff
Had a work call I needed to make so I Googled coffee shop near me and this is what popped up. I am so glad I pulled in. The breakfast option and coffee was delicious. Truly 10/10!
Absolutely the best espresso beans!

Excellent! We can't wait to come back for their pan de bono and fresh coffee. The team and owner are very caring and friendly, and the menu options are fun! The coffee itself is far better than the uptown staples.
Fresh Colombian coffee and wonderful empanadas.  So lucky this place was near my destination.  I will make it a point to return when back in town.

I had the best experience here! The young man made me a cafe mocha and it was incredible! What I loved most was the authenticity of the customer service and the story behind the brand. They have their own coffee farm in Columbia and there are pictures of the coffee farm along the wall.

This place is absolutely a hidden gem! They also sell their coffee at Daniel Stowe’s Conservatory.

This is absolutely one of my favorite places outside of Charlotte❤️

I stumbled upon this gem of a café in Mt. Holly and it instantly became one of my favorite spots. The coffee is incredible, smooth, rich, and full of flavor. It’s even more special knowing the beans are grown on their own farm in Colombia and roasted right here in Mt. Holly. You can really taste the care and quality in every cup.

The breakfast is fresh and delicious, and the empanadas are a must-try. They’re perfectly crisp on the outside, flavorful on the inside, and honestly some of the best I’ve ever had.

What really sets this café apart is their mission. They donate 5% of their profits to help fight hunger in Colombia, which makes supporting them feel even better.

If you're looking for amazing coffee, tasty food, and a place with purpose, this is it. Highly recommend!
We found a great little coffee shop on our way to Crowders mountain.  Perfect pit stop to fuel up!  Very welcoming and friendly people.  The coffee is amazing.  #supportlocal #supportsmallbusiness
Truly a gem and glad to have found this place. The owners are from Columbia and they have their coffee imported here. I recommend this place to anyone 💯

So pleasantly surprised by this place! The coffee was delicious- I’m gonna have to go back to buy some beans. I love that they sell their syrups, I went home and made a coffee with the syrup and it was great. Will def be back🖤

Gorgeous Coffee!
Wonderful owner!
Beautiful hearts!
Their a great morning and  mid day treat!  Their coffee, juice and eats are delicious, you’ll want to take extra Pan de Bono home. Very welcoming and great service.
Jade and Elise Obsidian Coffee is a favorite in my family. It is a family owned company with authentic coffee and food from Colombia. Everyone there is always welcoming and accommodating!
Best coffee in town.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Ricardo! I appreciate you are enjoying our coffee! Look forward to serve you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful locally owned coffee shop, with delicious New York style bagels, Colombian pastries and locally brewed kombucha!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you very much for visiting us! Look forward to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I was so happy to find their coffee shop opened since I'd gotten their coffee beans at a Christmas market this year. They were so nice and the empanadas were delicious. We tried every sauce option and all of them were delicious. The espresso shot was probably the best I've had in my life. Highly recommend getting some coffee beans and the jar of the hottest sauce while you're there. We got so much stuff just because it was all so good.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Kristen! I appreciate you loving our coffee! Look forward to see you again soon

reviews_data.review_text: I discovered Jade and Elise at the Belmont farmers market. They were parked under the trees in an unassuming black truck giving out flyers. I took a flyer and didn't think anything of it. I then met their daughter on the playground who was so kind and mature. I then went back and talked to her dad who was giving out the flyers and realised the kindness ran in the family. I decided to drive to their coffee shop, again in a very unassuming location, and bought this dark roast, ground "Espresso" for a maccineta. First I tried it on its own, then made it with warmed barrista oatly. I am not exaggerating when I say I haven't had coffee this good since I lived in the Bay Area. Moral of the story? Don't judge these guys by their cover. You won't regret it. And you'll be supporting a very special, humble, hard-working family.

reviews_data.review_text:
If only there were more places to sit. Coffee is fantastic and freshly done. They bring their own coffee from Columbia. There are a bunch of tasty treats, some filled with good eats (meats, fruits, cheese, and other yums). Vegetarians will be delighted in knowing that there are good options here.

My coffee was great, but I could have used a little more chocolate (mocha). I'll need to find my right options. The base latte is great for a lot of flavors or none at all

I tried the Pan de Bono. This had a nice semi-sweet and light crunch on the outside. The inside had a chewy cheese that could be great with other add-ons to your plate.

They have a catering food truck for events as well.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your feedback and I appreciate you stopping by! Look forward to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
Listen up, world—this isn’t just a coffee shop, it’s a caffeinated Colombian revolution that crowned me king of the bean! I strolled in expecting a solid brew, but what I got was a cup of liquid gold so epic I almost chest-bumped the barista and called him 'hermano.'
The vibes? Straight fire. The staff? Legends who brew like they’re forging Excalibur. I’m convinced this place is a secret coffee dojo because no mere mortal should wield this power.
AND they accept BITCOIN as payment!
